<br>
p + 11B ===&gt; 3(4He) +  8.7 MeV<br>
<br>
The cycle is aneutronic, which is very good meaning nothing gets turned radioactive.  Granted, you will still get cross reactions as protons convert into deuterium atoms.  However, the neutronic release is minimal.  This is kind of technically difficult to do, even more so than D-3He.<br>
<br>
Another good reaction is 3He + 3He ===&gt; 4He + 2p which is aneutronic as well and very difficult to do.  I can't recall the energy at this moment, but it compares with p + 11B.<br>
<br>
Why there is no 3He on Earth has everything to do with our atmosphere.  Helium is so light that it travels so fast at thermal temperatures that it can escape the gravitational pull of Earth.  The sun is bathing us in 3He all the time, and most of it gets pushed away by our magnetic field or quickly escapes.  The moon has no magnetic field or atmosphere, so they just embed themselves into the lunar surface.  Over billions of years, quite a stock has built up...enough to meet our energy needs for a few thousand years. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#484848><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace.showUserPublicProfile?gid=hamster@nuclearspace>Hamster</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator</span><br>  Posts: 802<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(2/3/03 1:49 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm25.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=124.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://image1ex.villagephotos.com/extern/935754.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.nuclearspace.com/ezboard/images/posticons/radman.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: re silly questions</span><hr size=1> It's also thought that the gas giants have a lot of 3He in thier atmospheres that we might be able to extract somehow.   <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace.showUserPublicProfile?gid=hamster@nuclearspace>Hamster</A> at: 2/3/03 2:21:23 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace.showUserPublicProfile?gid=dustyslaunchpad>Dustys Launchpad</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Space Cadet</span><br>  Posts: 50<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(2/3/03 9:39 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm25.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=124.topic&index=11>Reply</a> 